{
  "doc_id": "23817",
  "text": "Many works have shown the applicability of registration-based atlas propagation for the automatic segmentation, particularly in brain MR segmentation, where the multi-atlas propagation and segmentation (MAPS) has gained its wide popularity in recent years [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . In MAPS, each atlas is a combination of an intensity image and a label image. The intensity image is used for the registration process to map the space of the atlas to the unseen image, while the label image contains the segmentation information for propagation to the unseen image. The label image can also have prior knowledge such as the shape of the heart to assist the registration process [CITATION_6] .",
